NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Now, to the play. This hand is an excellent illustration of needing a plan. The hand can be made. Let's count winners. There are 5 spades, assuming a good break, 2 hearts and a club. That's only 8 tricks. However, we can also score 2 diamond ruffs for 2 more tricks. So, at trick 2, lead a diamond. Even if they win and play a trump, there are still 2 trumps left in dummy to trump 2 diamonds. In general, you should only draw trump immediately about 40% of the time. Probably the most common reason not to draw trump, as on this hand, is so that you can use dummy's trump to ruff losers. As a sound practice, you should look for it right away, particularly when dummy only has 3 cards in trump.|
