^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Now, let me discuss Eddy's opener. Many people like to open 1D with 4 diamonds and 5 clubs. The idea being it makes for an easier rebid over 1 of a major. I am not one of those people. In that area Lawrence and Bergen agree, and I disagree. Let me tell you why I prefer to open 1C. As you know I am a big LOTT fan. If you open 1D with 5/4 or 4/5 in diamonds and clubs, I will never know which. So, I think you should open 1C with 5 clubs and 4 diamonds, and agree that a 2C rebid can be done with 5 clubs. But that is just me. Most experts think that it is ok to open 1D on many hands with 4 diamonds and 5 clubs. But as Eddy says, most would open 1C with his particular hand since the clubs are very good, and the diamonds are not.|
