^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Now, assuming you play 1N by a passed hand is still forcing, Qian was attempting to show a limit raise with 3 trumps. Although he technically does have 10 points, because of his flat distribution, I would probably just bid 2H with his hand. On the other hand, certainly a limit raise is not unreasonable, particularly since he has 2 quick tricks. |
