NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|One final comment on the defense. It is an interesting question as to which spade Sandy should lead with 3 small. I am talking hypothetically here. If Sandy had three small spades, I suggest she lead low for the following reason. Partner has implicitly bid spades with her double and my rule when leading partner's suit when you have not supported is to lead count.|
PG| ***** 85 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|So, if partner bids a suit, you have not supported, and you have three small, you should lead low even if in general you lead high from 3 small. Because it turns out usually count provides more information when leading partner's suit. It is a different story when partner bids a suit and you support. Once you have supported, pard knows you have at least three. So, you lead high with no honor, low with an honor when you have three, always high with doubleton.|
