^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Well done Roberta. We discussed the bidding but let's talk about 4-4 vs 9 card fits. The conventional wisdom is that 4-4 fits play better. The reason for that is because the long suit can be used to throw off losers, which is what happened on this hand. However, a nine-card fit or even a 5-3 eight-card fit has one important advantage. If trumps break 4-1 in a 4-4 fit, declarer is usually in trouble. Whereas they rarely break 4-0 in a 9 card fit. And even with a 5-3 fit, if they break 4-0 at least declarer has one more trump than defender. |
