^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|As to the play. She did well to leave one trump out and play the diamonds. Basically, if diamonds do not break 3-3, she needs to trump a diamond on dummy. By playing diamonds instead of drawing the last trump, she gives herself extra chances to make 5. If I have 3 or more diamonds, she gets rid of her diamond loser. And if I only have 2 diamonds, she merely exchanges a trump trick for a diamond loser, so comes out even. So the diamond play was very good. However, once she sees that they break 3-3, she can then draw the last trump, before cashing the diamond and mking five.|
